    <stitle>STEERING COLUMN ASSEMBLY, TILT/TELESCOPING - REMOVE - STEERING COLUMN</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl0500903" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>STEERING COLUMN</title>
        <para>For most servicing procedures, it will be necessary to remove the steering column. This can be
            accomplished with the steering wheel in place or removed. Steering column removal can be completed as
            follows:
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Open hood.</para>
            <para>Mark position of universal joint to steering column shaft. Use for alignment on reassembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove pinch bolt from yoke at end of steering slip shaft. Separate the slip shaft from the
                yoke.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the steering wheel if the steering column is going to be replaced.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove turn signal control from steering column.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove trailer brake control from steering column.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect horn wire at the connector.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove four bolts, washers and nuts that attach the steering column bracket to the dash
                panel (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0500904">Figure 4</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0500904" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0500904" filename="../figg05/G0500904.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 4. Steering Column Removal</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. STEERING COLUMN</callout1>
                <callout1>2. BRACKET</callout1>
                <callout1>3. WASHER</callout1>
                <callout1>4. BOLT</callout1>
                <callout1>5. NUT</callout1>
                <callout1>6. UNIVERSAL JOINT</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Do not remove brackets from steering column. Brackets are part of the steering column assembly.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
    </svcproc>
